|===
| 1C |  1S  |
| 2C |  ?   |
|    | !2D! | inv. with {C} support
              {or} inv. with 6{OrMore}{xtimes}{S}
	      {or} inv. with 5*{S} & 5*{D}
	      {or} GF with no clear direction
|    | 2H   | natural, F1
|    | 3{lab}suit{rab} | natural GF
|===

[%autowidth,cols="^,2*<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1C |  1H  |
| 2C | {thinsp}? |
|    | !2D! | _similar to above_
|    | 2S   | GF with {S} values
|    | 3{lab}suit{rab} | natural GF
|===

&Opener's third bid&

After responder's 2D (other minor), opener's third bid follows similar
rules as those after fourth-suit forcing at the 2-level.

The difference is a rebid of 3C is non-forcing and bidding above it is
GF.

@ 2NT, or either previously-bid suit
_ = minimum strength, NF

@ other major (non-jump) = ambiguous strength, F1

@ bidding above 3C = extra strength, GF

