|  2C  | !2D! |
|  ?   |      |
| 2H   |      | Forcing, ambiguous strength
2+<| 2S,2NT,3C <| minimum, NF
2+<| 3D,3S,3NT <| extras, GF
|===

=== Opener rebids diamonds

When opener's suit is diamonds, we must avoid overloading 3C.
So two of the other major includes GF hands with values in the other
major but no-clear-direction.
_e.g._ on the first auction below, responder can rebid 2H with
[lightgrey-box]#{S}{thinsp}AKxx {H}{thinsp}KQx {D}{thinsp}Jxx {C}{thinsp}xxx#
